Class Robot

  • java.lang.Object
    • teamcode.Robot

  • public class Robot
extends java.lang.Object
    This class creates the robot object that consists of sensors, indicators, drive base and all the subsystems.

      • startMode

        public void startMode(TrcRobot.RunMode runMode)
        This method is call when the robot mode is about to start. It contains code to initialize robot hardware necessary for running the robot mode.
        Parameters:
        runMode - specifies the robot mode it is about to start, can be used to initialize mode specific hardware.

      • stopMode

        public void stopMode(TrcRobot.RunMode runMode)
        This method is call when the robot mode is about to end. It contains code to cleanup robot hardware before exiting the robot mode.
        Parameters:
        runMode - specifies the robot mode it is about to start, can be used to cleanup mode specific hardware.

      • traceStateInfo

        public void traceStateInfo(java.lang.Object state)
        This method is typically called in the autonomous state machine to log the autonomous state info as a state event in the trace log file. The logged event can be used to play back autonomous path movement.
        Parameters:
        state - specifies the current state of the state machine.
